In this section, we will learn to how implement a binary tree.     

First let's checkout the structure of a node in binary tree:

```cpp
int val;
node left;
node right;
```

Note that similar to linked list, the node contains an integer value and left/right pointers for children nodes rather than next since this is a non-linear data structure. If there is no node present at left/right pointer, it is initialized as null.      


